00:51:51,150 --> 00:51:56,406
- Yeah, let me get these bad boys up.
- This shit be cool, dog.

702
00:51:56,489 --> 00:51:58,157
Share the sodas, too.

703
00:52:03,788 --> 00:52:05,873
- What's up?
- Hey.

704
00:52:08,084 --> 00:52:10,128
What's up?

705
00:52:10,211 --> 00:52:13,214
- Let me holler at you real quick.
- What up?

706
00:52:14,632 --> 00:52:17,427
- You did like I said?
- Yeah.

707
00:52:17,510 --> 00:52:22,390
Yeah, you must have, because the nigger
went up. He ain't never coming back down.

708
00:52:22,473 --> 00:52:26,144
Chris and snoop... pow!

709
00:52:26,227 --> 00:52:30,606
- What?
- Look. Just be cool, all right?

710
00:52:34,986 --> 00:52:38,781
- Our heroes back from the wars.
- Got those poll numbers yet?

711
00:52:38,865 --> 00:52:45,330
Not too bad, either. Royce 35,
you 26, gray 20.19% undecided.

712
00:52:45,413 --> 00:52:47,749
We're fucked
if we haven't moved more than that.

713
00:52:47,832 --> 00:52:51,252
I need to be at 30
and I need Tony taking 25 of his points.

714
00:52:51,336 --> 00:52:56,174
Royce's negatives are way up.
34% unfavorable to 43% favorable?

715
00:52:56,299 --> 00:52:59,302
- He's vulnerable.
- Geri, understand this.

716
00:52:59,385 --> 00:53:03,514
To win, I need Tony gray to take
a huge bite out of Royce's lead.

717
00:53:03,598 --> 00:53:06,642
Tony's moved, what?
Two points in the last month?

718
00:53:06,726 --> 00:53:09,812
That poll says one in five voters
hasn't decided yet.

719
00:53:09,896 --> 00:53:14,776
Yeah. The radio spots worked magic.
How much money we piss away on those?

720
00:53:14,901 --> 00:53:17,278
Look at these first district figures.

721
00:53:17,362 --> 00:53:21,240
That's my base and I'm polling
37% with 24% undecided?

722
00:53:21,324 --> 00:53:24,494
- Fuck me! I'm done!
- Nobody's focused on this race yet.

723
00:53:24,660 --> 00:53:28,456
- We're gonna own the first.
- Look at Royce in the fourth.

724
00:53:28,539 --> 00:53:32,668
- Tony needs west Baltimore.
- He needs to be rounding 25%

725
00:53:32,794 --> 00:53:34,170
and headed for 30.

726
00:53:34,253 --> 00:53:35,296
And, by the way,

727
00:53:35,380 --> 00:53:39,342
who can tell me when the fuck did
the sixth district become 64% black?

728
00:53:39,425 --> 00:53:41,886
About five years ago
in the last redistricting.

729
00:53:41,969 --> 00:53:45,640
Mostly, as I recall, to give your
ass more white votes in the first.

730
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:49,394
What the fuck was I thinking?

731
00:53:49,477 --> 00:53:52,313
A lot can happen
between now and election day.

732
00:53:52,397 --> 00:53:54,732
I've been ahead further
than Royce is and lost.

733
00:53:58,861 --> 00:54:00,863
I can't win this.

734
00:54:02,490 --> 00:54:04,909
Tommy, where the fuck you going?

735
00:54:04,992 --> 00:54:06,911
I'm your ride home, man.

736
00:54:13,167 --> 00:54:15,253
The man can read a poll.

737
00:55:25,573 --> 00:55:29,160
- You been drinking?
- I'm fine.

738
00:55:29,243 --> 00:55:33,498
Well, you need to be fine somewhere else.
Park curfew is midnight.

739
00:55:33,748 --> 00:55:38,878
City's averaging a murder a day
and you're quoting park rules?

740
00:55:38,961 --> 00:55:43,257
- What are you, a smart ass?
- Sorry. I didn't mean nothing.

741
00:55:47,053 --> 00:55:48,679
Don't I know you?

742
00:55:49,972 --> 00:55:51,933
I'm running for mayor.

743
00:55:52,975 --> 00:55:55,436
Tommy carcetti, first district.

744
00:55:56,437 --> 00:55:59,273
I'll come back through
in about 20, councilman.

745
00:55:59,357 --> 00:56:02,193
Do me a favor and take it down the road.

746
00:57:02,169 --> 00:57:04,755
- Randy?
- Yes, ma'am.

